gptanswer: [Solution] We can factor the denominator as a difference of squares: $$45^2 - 38^2 = (45+38)(45-38) = 83 \cdot 7.$$ Therefore, we have $$\dfrac{7}{45^2 - 38^2} = \dfrac{7}{83 \cdot 7} = \boxed{\dfrac{1}{83}}.$$
